If I call Mouse.GetState(), then the game won't exit unless I move the mouse or press a key after Game.Exit is called, suggesting that something is waiting for an input event. Git bisect revealed me that this problem was actually introduced by commit https://github.com/opentk/opentk/commit/1cf7386748a09cf3205d3e1cd0db72f013693c1f

To reproduce the issue, run the following testcase on Linux and press Esc, without moving the mouse or pressing anything else (pressing and holding esc for too long might make it hard to reproduce).

```
        protected override void Update (GameTime gameTime)
        {
            var kbState = Keyboard.GetState();
            if (kbState.IsKeyDown(Keys.Escape)) {
                Exit ();
            }
            // Comment the line below and the game exits correctly
            Console.WriteLine (Mouse.GetState());
            base.Update (gameTime);
        }
```

I've noticed that even calling Console.WriteLine (Mouse.GetState()); only once (during the Initialize function) is enough to trigger the issue.
